  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\n   The verifier reports
\"Instruction does not dominate all uses!\" for values produced by:\n   -
experimental.vp.strided.load\n   - masked.gather\n   used as operands to
llvm.vector.insert. This indicates the SLP vectorizer emitted a use
(vector_insert) at a point in the block that precedes the definition(s) of the
sub-vector producers (the vector loads/gathers), violating SSA dominance.\n\n
In this reproducer, SLP builds a vector by inserting sub-vectors produced by
vectorized loads (strided/gather). The vector_insert is emitted before those
sub-vectors are defined.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\n   The provided log shows
that the verifier fails immediately after SLP runs. The broken IR includes:\n   -
%6 = call <4 x i16> @llvm.experimental.vp.strided.load...\n   - %4 = call <8 x
i16> @llvm.vector.insert... %6\n   and similarly for @llvm.masked.gather. The
verifier error says the defs (%6/%7) do not dominate their uses (the
vector.insert calls). This directly points to an insertion point ordering bug in
SLP's code emission.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\n   - Build of the final vector
from sub-vectors happens in BoUpSLP::processBuildVector via
ShuffleInstructionBuilder::finalize(), which calls createInsertVector(...) to
generate llvm.vector.insert or equivalent shuffles.\n   - For gather nodes that
stitch together already-vectorized subtrees (CombinedEntriesWithIndices), SLP
first vectorizes those subtrees by calling vectorizeTree() for each combined
entry (createBuildVector() does this explicitly at lines ~17410-17414).\n   - The
insertion point for the gather node is set via
BoUpSLP::setInsertPointAfterBundle(E) only with respect to E's own bundle (lines
~16131+). It does not account for the last instruction in the bundles of the
combined subtrees.\n   - vectorizeTree for each subtree uses its own
InsertPointGuard and sets insertion just after the last scalar in that subtree's
bundle; vectorized loads/gathers are therefore emitted at that position, which
can be later in the block than the gather's insertion point.\n   - After the
subtrees are vectorized, control returns to the gather, and the builder insertion
point is restored to the gather's position (earlier). Emitting vector_insert
there causes the use-before-def: vector_insert uses the sub-vector value produced
by a load/gather that appears later in the block.\n\n   In short:
setInsertPointAfterBundle(E) only considers E; for gather nodes that insert
sub-vectors from other entries, we must emit after the latest of E and all
combined entries to preserve dominance.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s)\n   - File:
llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\n   - Function:
BoUpSLP::setInsertPointAfterBundle(const TreeEntry *E)\n   - Change: When E is a
gather and has CombinedEntriesWithIndices, compute the last instruction across E
and all combined entries' bundles and set insertion after the latest. This
ensures that any sub-vector producers (e.g., masked gather, vp.strided.load)
already dominate the subsequent llvm.vector.insert that consumes them.\n\n
Patch (inserted after acquiring LastInst for E and before computing
LastInstIt):\n\n   --- before ---\n   Instruction *LastInst =
&getLastInstructionInBundle(E);\n   assert(LastInst && \"Failed to find last
instruction in bundle\");\n   BasicBlock::iterator LastInstIt =
LastInst->getIterator();\n   \n   --- after ---\n   Instruction *LastInst =
&getLastInstructionInBundle(E);\n   assert(LastInst && \"Failed to find last
instruction in bundle\");\n   \n   // If we are about to build a vector from
sub-vectors (combined entries),\n   // ensure we emit after the latest
contributing bundle to preserve dominance.\n   if (E->isGather() &&
!E->CombinedEntriesWithIndices.empty()) {\n     for (const auto &P :
E->CombinedEntriesWithIndices) {\n       const TreeEntry *SubE =
VectorizableTree[P.first].get();\n       Instruction *Cand =
&getLastInstructionInBundle(SubE);\n       if (LastInst->getParent() ==
Cand->getParent() &&\n           LastInst->comesBefore(Cand))\n         LastInst
= Cand;\n     }\n   }\n   \n   BasicBlock::iterator LastInstIt =
LastInst->getIterator();\n\n   This mirrors the existing PHI/landing pad handling
that follows and keeps debug location behavior. By selecting the latest bundle
tail among E and its combined sub-entries (when in the same block), subsequent
inserts (vector_insert/shuffles) will be placed after the definitions of the
sub-vectors (e.g., masked.gather/vp.strided.load).\n\n   Rationale:\n   -
vectorizeTree() of sub-entries runs before finalize emission in
processBuildVector(). Those nested calls insert their instructions at their own
post-bundle IP. By moving the gather emission IP to be after the maximum of all
bundle tails, we ensure defs precede uses. If both pick the same position, the
nested vectorizeTree inserted first; the gather inserts later, thus keeping a
valid order.\n\n5. Conclusion:\n   The crash is due to a dominance violation when
emitting llvm.vector.insert for gather nodes that insert sub-vectors produced by
later-emitted vector loads/gathers. Adjusting setInsertPointAfterBundle() to
account for the latest last-in-bundle across the gather and its combined entries
ensures the final vector build is emitted after all its sub-vector producers.
This preserves SSA dominance and fixes the verifier failure for both
vp.strided.load and masked.gather cases.",
